    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Getting a Handle On the Beach Boys' Sandals</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Drew Muckley letter corrects lyrics to Beach Boys' song Surfin' USA in June 4 article about surfing apparel (S)0</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Not that I haven't botched lyrics to a song in my life. I sang ''You and me and Leslie'' to the Rascals' tune ''Groovin' '' for years until I sheepishly discovered that it was actually ''You and me, endlessly.'' Just wanted to share that in ''Surfin' U.S.A.'' by the Beach Boys, the line actually tells us that ''We'll all be wearin' our baggies, huarache sandals, too,'' -- not ''Archie'' sandals (''Dry 'n' Wild,'' June 4). Huaraches -- sandals with leather uppers and tire-tread soles -- have been indigenous to the surfer look since the 60's.</p>
        <p>DREW MUCKLEY  Red Bank</p>
      </block>
